commit.message: _augeas.c (augeas_get): work around a bug in aug_get

Add alternative bindings

When calling Augeas::create, we return bindings that behave more
Ruby-ish. To this end, we set up a class Augeas::Facade, an instance of
which is returned by Augeas::create

The C bindings in _augeas.c have a few methods to undo some of the return
value munging that the old bindings do so that the Ruby code for
Augeas::Facade can easily create targeted exceptions reflecting the error,
based on the result from aug_error.

The tests in tests/tc_facade.rb are the same that were used for the augeas
gem, maintained in the fork at https://github.com/dotdoom/augeas. They pass
which means that Augeas::Facade is a complete replacement for the bindings
in that repo.

_augeas.c: add missing error codes

There are a few new error codes that have not been added to the bindings yet
.travis.yml: put build notifications in the #augeas IRC channel

Add building against Ruby 2.0.0 and 2.3.1 to Travis

Ruby 2.0.0 is shipped in CentOS 7, and 2.3.1 is the currently latest available
Add a Gemfile
* README.md: restructure a bit and include build instructions
README.md: reformat as markdown

* _augeas.c: fix some compiler warnings

There were a couple places where we got the warning
  warning: ISO C90 forbids mixed declarations and code [-Wdeclaration-after-statement]

Change the code to move declarations up before actual code
* NEWS: correct date for 0.5.0 release
Prepare NEWS, AUTHORS and Rakefile for 0.5.0
* Rakefile: replace deprecated rdoc/gem rake tasks
Add Travis CI settings

Expose changes in Augeas 1.0.0 release

  * ext/augeas/_augeas.c: add Augeas#label, Augeas#rename, Augeas#text_retrieve
    and Augeas#text_store
  * lib/augeas.rb: add ".lns" suffix if a module name is passed to
    Augeas#transform to match aug_transform behaviour;
    add Augeas#clearm, #touch to mirror aug_srun commands;
    add Augeas#context= and #context to access /augeas/context
* .gitignore: ignore build files

Expose aug_srun as Augeas#srun

  * ext/augeas/_augeas.c: add Augeas#srun
  * ext/augeas/_augeas.h: split out header, add memstream utils from Augeas
  * tests/tc_augeas.rb: added test case for 'srun'

* ext/augeas/extconf.rb: add libxml2 headers and library to Makefile
* ruby-augeas.spec: add build req on libxml2-devel

* AUTHORS: updating list of contributors
* Rakefile: adding gem authors metadata, now mandatory
* tests/root/etc/ssh/sshd_config: needed to run the tests

Released version 0.4.1

The only reason to do this release is that the tarball for 0.4.0 contained
object files from my local machine.
ruby-augeas.spec: update to require augeas-0.8.0
Released version 0.4.0
Rakefile(dist): make work with git
Expose aug_span as Augeas#span
Augeas#error: expose the aug_error functions

Exposed 'setm' function in ruby API

Added ruby API call for 'setm'.
Added tests for 'setm'.
* lib/augeas.rb (transform): simplified
* lib/augeas.rb (set): do not call to_a on values, since it's already an array

'set' sets multiple elements

The 'set' function has been extended to set multiple elements at the
same time.

  * ext/augeas/_augeas.c: renamed the 'set' function from the API
    to 'set_internal'
  * lib/augeas.rb:  added new 'set' function, changed 'set!' correspondingly,
    made other function use 'set_internal' when necessary
  * tests/tc_augeas.rb, tests/root/etc/group: added tests for new
    function 'set'
Release 0.3.0
